description: The abbreviated form or code representing the state where the block group is located.
The geometric representation of the block group as a polygon, defined by its boundary coordinates.
A code that uniquely identifies the block group within a census tract.
A unique identifier combining the state, county, and tract codes to represent the block group's location.
A code that identifies the census tract to which the block group belongs.
The amount of land area covered by the block group.
The longitude coordinate of the block group's centroid.
The name of the state where the block group is located.
The name or label assigned to the block group.
The MAF/TIGER Feature Class Code, which categorizes the geographic feature represented by the block group.
The name of the county where the block group is situated.
The year associated with the geographical data of the block group.
The amount of water area (such as lakes, rivers, or oceans) within the boundaries of the block group.
The latitude coordinate of the block group's centroid, which represents the central point of the block group.
A unique identifier for a specific block group within a geographic area.
The precise point location (latitude and longitude) of the block group's centroid.
The functional status of the block group, indicating its statistical purpose.
The Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS) code that represents the state where the block group is located.
The FIPS code that identifies the county where the block group is situated.
